s-serif">A lot of the legal action in crypto in the U.S. is about whether v=
arious crypto things are securities. If a crypto thing is a security, then =
it basically needs to be=C2=A0(1)=C2=A0registered with the U.S. Securities =
and Exchange Commission, (2) only sold to =E2=80=9Caccredited investors=E2=
=80=9D (with $1 million of net worth or $200,000 of annual income)=C2=A0or =
(3) not offered in the U.S. If it=E2=80=99s not a security, then there=E2=
=80=99s a lot more flexibility to sell it and trade it widely.</p><p style=
=3D"margin:16px 0px;font-family:Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif">Some crypto thi=
ngs are securities, some are not, and a lot are sort of unclear. Bitcoin is=
 not a security. Ethereum is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
